I"‹<p>Thanassis is a postdoctoral research scholar in the nuclear astrophysics group at the <a href="https://tunl.duke.edu/">Triangle Universities Nuclear Laboratory</a> and <a href="https://physics.sciences.ncsu.edu/">North Carolina State University</a> working with Profs. <a href="https://iliadis.web.unc.edu/">Christian Iliadis</a> and <a href="https://rlongland.github.io/">Richard Longland</a>. He earned his Ph.D. from <a href="http://www.physics.mcmaster.ca/">McMaster University</a> under the supervision of Prof. <a href="http://www.physics.mcmaster.ca/~chenal/nuc_astro_struc/personal/">Alan Chen</a> in experimental nuclear astrophysics.</p>

<p>His area of expertise is <a href="/research">nuclear astrophysics</a>, a cross-disciplinary field delving into the intricate relationship between stellar evolution and the creation of chemical elements in the universe.</p>

<p>Apart from his research, Thanassis enthusiastically participates in various <a href="/outreach">science outreach</a> activities and channels his passion for subjects spanning science, philosophy, art, and other captivating themes through his <a href="/blog">personal blog</a>.</p>
